reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little blocks for the Minecraft fans
reviews.reviewText: These magnetic blocks are a little pricey but my son loves them! Make sure to read the full description! These are 1 inch blocks and the set only comes with 40something (I forgot how many exactly). You will need at least 2 sets to have enough blocks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for kids who love Minecraft
reviews.reviewText: Bought this as a Christmas gift for my 5 and 6 year old boys. They love Minecraft, and absolutely loved these to build their own Minecraft world to play with their Minecraft toys they got. Smaller than expected, but totally worth it. My boys already asked if they can have more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: While my boys love these blocks the photo is VERY MISLEADING. Note that the photo is most like 2-3 sets and they are smaller than appears. My boys were disappointed when they arrived compared to what we saw in the photo regardless of it saying 54. Again not what the picture depicted

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: So these are expensive. Neat toy and honestly really cool however I should have read how many blocks one order comes with. The pictures are a little misleading. You can not build that with the blocks you get. You get so few blocks it's honestly kind of hard to build much with one set so it's a little disappointing. I would give less stars for being misled but I should have read better I guess and the quality is good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars MY KIDS LOVE THESE
reviews.reviewText: I have a two year old and a 6 year old who both love to play with. They are about an inch square. They can build things with them on the refrigerator, doors, and with other magnetic toys like magna tiles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The magnets are great and my kids were excited to start playing with them, but they’re little and not worth $1 ea. The picture is also misleading. You cannot build much with 54 blocks, although that sounds like a good amount.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My 13 yo is autistic is so in love with these bought multiples and he is busy for hours "Santa" got him a big set and he says it was his favorite gift even over a xbox

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Deceiving and not worth the price
reviews.reviewText: This was quite disappointing especially on Christmas morning. When this was purchased it looked as if it would be a complete set that a child could build and enjoy, unfortunately it doesn't even come with enough blocks to fully build anything that is even displayed in the booklet it comes with. You can't even build the image displayed on the box itself which is what's advertised. My son was extremely disappointed when he realized he didn't have enough to build the images in the booklet. I am only giving two stars because the blocks quality themselves is decent
